‡¶∂‡ßÅ‡¶∞‡ßÅ ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡¶æ ‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ï‚Ä¶

‡¶¨‡ßá‡¶∏‡¶ø‡¶ï Kubectl ‡¶ï‡¶Æ‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßç‡¶°:

* Get Resources: kubectl get pods/services/deployments
- pods, services, ‡¶Ö‡¶•‡¶¨‡¶æ deployments ‡¶è‡¶∞ ‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü ‡¶ì ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶ü‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶ü‡¶æ‡¶∏ ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶æ‡¶Ø‡¶º‡•§

* Create Resource: kubectl create -f [config.yaml]
- YAML ‡¶´‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶≤ ‡¶•‡ßá‡¶ï‡ßá Pod/Service ‡¶§‡ßà‡¶∞‡¶ø ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá.

* Delete Resource: kubectl delete -f [config.yaml]
- YAML ‡¶´‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶¨‡¶≤‡ßá ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ì‡¶Ø‡¶º‡¶æ ‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßã‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶∏‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶°‡¶ø‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶ü ‡¶ï‡¶∞‡ßá ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶Ø‡¶º.

* Describe Resource: kubectl describe pod/service/deployment [name]
- ‡¶è‡¶ï‡¶ü‡¶ø ‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶™‡ßá‡¶∏‡¶ø‡¶´‡¶ø‡¶ï pod, service, or deployment ‡¶∏‡¶Æ‡ßç‡¶™‡¶∞‡ßç‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶∏‡ßç‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶∞‡¶ø‡¶§ ‡¶§‡¶•‡ßç‡¶Ø ‡¶¶‡ßá‡¶ñ‡¶æ‡¶Ø‡¶º‡•§

* Logs from a Container: kubectl logs [pod_name]
